Step 1 : Add news section to homepage template
<section class="news-section">
    <h2>Ltest News</h2>

    <div class="news-item">
      <h3> New Menu Launch!</h3>
      <p>We're excited to announce our brand-new seasonal menu featuring frsh local ingredients. Come try it this weekend!</p>
      <span class="news-date">August 9, 2025</span>
    </div>

    <div class="news-item">
       <h3> Anniversary Celebration</h3>
       <p>Join us for our 2nd anniversary celebration with live music and special discounts all day!</p>
       <span class="news-date">July 15, 2025</span>
    </div>
</section>

Step 2 : Style with CSS 
.news-section {
    background-color: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 20px;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 30px auto;
    border-radius: 8px;
}

.news-section h2 {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    color: #333;
}

.news-item h3 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    color: #ff6347;
}

.news-date p{
    color: #555
    margin-bottom: 6px;
}

.news-date {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #888;
}

Step 3 : Link CSS in base template
{% load static %}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{% static 'css/style.css' %}">

****Result****
> Clean "Latest News" box with announcements
> Each news item has a little title, description, and date
> Hardcoded now, but styled so you can easily make it dynamic later

